</section>

<!-- ============ 02 · THE PROTOCOL ============ -->
<section id="protocol">
  <div class="wrap sec-grid">
    <div class="sec-label">§ <span class="n">02</span> · The Protocol</div>
    <div>
      <p class="bigp rv">It goes in and takes over. <span class="dim">Four phases, on a loop, forever.</span></p>
      <div class="loop rv d1">
        <div class="ph">
          <div class="n">Phase 01</div>
          <h3>Assess.</h3>
          <p>Osprey reads everything: the stack, the books, the inboxes, the funnels, the deploy logs. It maps what's broken, what's leaking, and what's quietly costing you money. Nothing stays hidden.</p>
          <span class="arr">→</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ph">
          <div class="n">Phase 02</div>
          <h3>Execute.</h3>
          <p>It doesn't file a ticket. It fixes the thing. Patches the checkout, chases the late payer, rebalances the spend, reclaims the hours. Before your standup, not after your quarter.</p>
          <span class="arr">→</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ph">
          <div class="n">Phase 03</div>
          <h3>Build.</h3>
          <p>Then it builds what should have existed all along: the dashboard, the pipeline, the report engine, the automation. Proprietary, single-tenant, yours. The business gets new organs.</p>
          <span class="arr">→</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ph">
          <div class="n">Phase 04</div>
          <h3>Compound.</h3>
          <p>Every correction is written to memory at high priority. Every win becomes policy. It never repeats a mistake and never starts from zero. Week over week it gets sharper, not stale.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="versus rv d2">
        <div class="col a">
          <div class="tag">A chatbot</div>
          <h3>Waits. Answers. <span class="ghost">Forgets.</span></h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Waits for you to prompt it, every single time.</li>
            <li>Hands a suggestion back to a human to action.</li>
            <li>Forgets the conversation the moment it ends.</li>
            <li>Starts from zero, every morning, forever.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col b">
          <div class="tag">Osprey</div>
          <h3>Doesn't wait. Doesn't forget. <span class="it">Executes.</span></h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Moves work forward across seven brands at once, unprompted.</li>
            <li>Holds real keys to real systems. Read access is the floor.</li>
            <li>Every conversation it has ever had is permanently searchable.</li>
            <li>Gets sharper every week instead of needing to be retrained.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="exec-list rv d2">
        <div class="hd">A partial log. Nobody asked for any of it.</div>
        <p class="exec-line">Deployed the code<span class="sep">·</span>restarted the servers<span class="sep">·</span>pulled the ad numbers<span class="sep">·</span>built the <em>branded PDF</em><span class="sep">·</span>sent the email<span class="sep">·</span>refreshed the spend pacer <em>at 1 AM</em><span class="sep">·</span>wrote the <em>weekly brand report.</em></p>
      </div>
