<!-- ============ 03 · THE ARCHITECTURE ============ -->
<section>
  <div class="wrap sec-grid">
    <div class="sec-label">§ <span class="n">03</span> · The Architecture</div>
    <div>
      <p class="bigp rv">What makes it an <span class="it">operating system</span> rather than a smart assistant <span class="dim">comes down to four things working together.</span></p>
      <div style="margin-top:76px">
        <div class="pillar rv">
          <div class="no">Spec. 01</div>
          <div><h3>Memory that <span class="it">compounds.</span></h3><div class="sub">Permanent · searchable · shared</div></div>
          <p>Every conversation it has ever had is permanently searchable. Durable facts load into every interaction, and a shared semantic mesh means knowledge learned in one corner of the business is available everywhere. <b>It never starts from zero.</b></p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar rv">
          <div class="no">Spec. 02</div>
          <div><h3>Learns from <span class="it">being corrected.</span></h3><div class="sub">Once is enough</div></div>
          <p>Tell it it's wrong once and that correction is written to memory at high priority. It doesn't make that mistake again. <b>Over weeks it gets sharper, not stale.</b></p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar rv">
          <div class="no">Spec. 03</div>
          <div><h3>Commands a team, <span class="it">not just itself.</span></h3><div class="sub">An AI org chart, one brain on top</div></div>
          <p>Osprey sits on top of a fleet of specialized agents: one running inbound leads, one for each brand in the portfolio, an executive assistant running the founder's calendar. <b>It coordinates all of them.</b></p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar rv">
          <div class="no">Spec. 04</div>
          <div><h3>Operates with <span class="it">discipline.</span></h3><div class="sub">Verified · scoped · auditable</div></div>
          <p>It can't confidently lie. It is forced to verify before claiming something's broken or stating a number. It stays in its lane, never bleeds one brand's data into another, and does exactly what's asked instead of freelancing. <b>That's what makes it safe enough to hand the keys to.</b></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

